From edd at debian.org  Tue Apr 24 14:52:42 2007
From: edd at debian.org (Dirk Eddelbuettel)
Date: Tue, 24 Apr 2007 07:52:42 -0500
Subject: [R-sig-Debian] R 2.5.0 in Debian unstable
Message-ID: <17965.64922.656760.716843@basebud.nulle.part>


I just uploaded R 2.5.0 to Debian's unstable distribution.  As Peter's
announcement says, it now contains two new packages'rcompgen' and
'codetools'.

About two or three weeks ago, I also packaged these, just like other
'recommended' packages as r-cran-rcompgen and r-cran-codetools. However, as
"new" packages, they are still in the NEW queue awaiting inclusion into
Debian.  If you find rcompgen and/or codetools lacking, I'd recommend a
direct installation via install.packages() from inside R 2.5.0 until the
packages hit out mirror.

Feedback, questions, ... welcome.

Best regards, Dirk

